Description: Quantafuel ASA is a Norway-based recycling company, that converts post-consumer plastic waste back into low-carbon synthetic oil products replacing virgin oil products in the production of new plastics, as well as development and operation in related services. The Company establishes, operates and owns dedicated Plastic-to-Liquid (PtL) plants and plastic sorting facilities. Quantafuel has two plants in operation: Skive (Denmark) for chemical recycling and Kristiansund (Norway) for combined mechanical and chemical recycling. The Company is focused on building a circular economy for plastics that increases resource utilization and reduces emissions.
